    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Decorative wood from the species Andira inermis found in the West Indies. It is a reddish brown to black figured wood that is highly resistant to fungi and insects, used for making walking sticks and cabinetwork.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
